{
  "texts": [
    "253 Bernstein et al. [272] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" refers to chatbot outputs that sound convincingly plausible yet are factually inaccurate.",
    "Continued on next pageTABLE V -continued from previous page Num.",
    "Author(s) Year Application Definition Citation 254 Heck [273] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" refers to ChatGPT providing text that combines real and fabricated evidence, resulting in plausible answers, occasionally appearing as nonsense when assessed according to the common knowledge of experts in different areas, also called \"mistakes.\"",
    "\"Intrinsic hallucinations\" occur when the generation output contradicts the source content.",
    "\"Extrinsic hallucinations\" occur when the output can neither be supported nor contradicted by the source."
  ]
}